title: Lazuli: History
author: Ace_of_Knaves
pages:
#- 

§l   Lazuli: History§r

            by

§o        NateMagic§r
#- From my arrival in Lazuli to the Jacks second attack is as follows:

Lazuli had just previously made a truce with the Pumpkin Jacks 24 hours ago. Toshibi the snake was the pioneer of this treaty. We will discover why he
#- did this later on in this chapter. Let's go back in time for now. The Jacks started off in Lazuli playing peacefully and subverting the town. Their members somewhat kept to themselves though withdrawing from events that the townsfolk did 
#- together. They were gathering materials as they decided that they wanted to be the enemy in CivCraft. 
#- Their plan was to set off TnT and blow the whole senate up and destroy most of the roads in Lazuli. They decided they would do it when no one was online, to avoid the compromise of someone discovering them when they were planting all of the TnT charges. 
#- After all the charges were set then they would proceed to detonate the town when players were online. 
#- The day had come they finally had the material and waited till everyone had went to bed in the United States. They were a European group so the time zones would make the terrorism easy enough to pull of. Yes, the Jacks originally wanted 
#- to be a terrorist cell. As they started planting charges they had all spread out over the town and Mindscale logged in and spotted one of them planting a charge. He wondered what they were doing so he walked over and saw the row of TnT. One of the 
#- Jacks flipped the TnT switch and somewhat blew up the senate. They, for the most part destroyed their own homes in Lazuli. Then they fled Lazuli. 
#- Mindscale passed the word on to the Council of Lazuli. War was declared between the Pumpkin Jacks and Lazuli. Toshibi on the council did not want to fight, he had other plans. He alone talked to the Jacks and formed a cease fire with them. Toshibi 
#- failed to relay this message to the Council, on purpose? Maybe, but that I do not know. A group of bloodthirsty Lazulians set out to attack the Jacks. They found them in a tower that would eventually be recognized as an innocent player's 
#- house. The Lazulians raided that house and attacked the Jacks who were using the house's grinders without the owner's permission. The Lazulians assumed this house was one of the Jacks' strongholds. The Jack's fled this tower. 
#- <I am unaware of anything that happened from the end of the attack on the tower to my arrival>

Time passed and NateMagic arrived into Lazuli with his group. Lazuli was now looking more powerful, with 10
#- new citizens all with diamond gear. NateMagic's band of warriors set out to find the Jacks after hearing that they were a bunch of terrorists. He was quickly called off by Lazulians who said he would just get killed. So NateMagic returned to 
#- Lazuli and started working with Lem0nland, Ttocs, SomethingSaucy, and Toshibi, some contact with ryker. NateMagic worked on building a snitch network and the eventual construction of a wall around Lazuli. The wall's reason was to give Lazuli 
#- something to do. It would log when people broke into Lazuli without using the entrances provided, and it would show where attackers were entering the city. NateMagic's crew worked on a birch wood ship they just decided to build one day as laws in 
#- Lazuli prevented them from making a house without buying land. (Ship on water, so no need to buy land.) 
#- Infinius Arrives:

Infinius, Scylla's gang arrives in Lazuli mid-afternoon. They burn and destroy everything in their wake. They break into Toshibi's vault, into the Lazulian vault, and NateMagic and his crew's ship was already burning 
#- as the prior night of building the wooden ship a lightning storm occurred. (The ship went up in flames and NateMagic and Squiotle logged out and would just tell Alexzandria what happened, as it was her master design.) Infinius avoided the burning mass of 
#- wood in the water as it looked like it had already been ransacked. Little did they know this ship had multiple stacks of diamond blocks just stored out in the open. 
#- Dealing with the Fallout:

he raids were over and the city was left empty, it seems they had hit every single chest worth stealing from, all vaults broken into. (At this point in time no one in Lazuli really thought to make 
#- massive obsidian vaults at bedrock for their wealth, they just hid it underground.) NateMagic got online to see that the whole city had been raided and quickly told Alexzandria that Infinius burnt the ship down, not Sqouitle and 
#- himself the night prior. Laughing at the convenience he got online to see blizzxx arguing with Toshibi. Toshibi was screaming at the top of his lungs that all his wealth was gone while blizz was admiring how the city was raided. Toshibi announced that 
#- all hackers/xrayers should be banned and everything that happened should be reversed. While blizz being as dense as he is told Toshibi to go fuck himself and that griefing is a valid play style. Toshibi then raged and started attacking blizz. Then told 
#- Lem0nland to KoS NateMagic and his crew. Toshibi didn't realize that NateMagic had networked himself into the town and everyone was questioning it. NateMagic summoned squoitle online and they went to town on Toshibi. Toshibi was 
#- caught trying to escape them jumping up a hill while firing arrows at them. He was eating melons as sqouitle cut him down. 
#- The Fortitude of Lazuli

NateMagic, Lem0nland, and Logic_Man were building Lazuli back up. NateMagic had rebuilt his ship out of obsidian. Logic_Man was paving roads and creating new developments for Lazuli.
#- Lem0nland was creating massive amounts of potions and building an Arena for Lazuli, while trying to organize a military. Things were going smoothly for the still in ruins city. Delbunk the Evil was creating a massive Columbian style building right 
#- outside of the Lazuli portal. All was well. 
#- The Jacks Attack: A City still Recovering 

NateMagic sitting on his ship watching his cameras looking for new people arriving in the city, then saw a mass of players rushing in from the east. They had come from Winterfell (Notsoblue's 
#- Castle). NateMagic sounding the alarm waving to the Jacks' as they pour into his city messaging the only two members online, Ttocs and Lalleholm. They both made their way onto the ship. 
#- Lalleholm's mind:

Finally my chance to betray them. Lalleholm had been the spy for the Jacks the entire time building a really bad looking cobblestone house had told the Jacks that the town was at it's weakest point. He was to 
#- set down a chest and fill it with potions telling NateMagic and Ttoc's to get the potions. While in the chest NateMagic and Ttoc's would be showered by harming 2's by Lalleholm. Lalleholm panic'd as he saw NateMagic atop of the boat alongside Ttocs 
#- Khan. Upon entering the boat his mind went blank. Ttocs Khan turned his back and he struck. 
#- The battle:

NateMagic heard the sound of Lalleholm's sword colliding with Ttocs Khan's back. He quickly turned and slew the traitor on the spot without a second thought. The Jacks were making their way through town looking for
#- people to murder saving the boat for last as they knew it would be impossible to defeat Ttocs and NateMagic together. Ttocs Khan grew angry as he did not know there was no one in the town online at that given moment jumped the side of the boat. 
#- NateMagic looked at him and let the Khan go. Sitting on the boat waiting for the Jack's to come NateMagic stashed Lalleholm's pearl away. Three Jacks then arrived, aphedias and two others. They started to pillar dirt up the cannons on the side of the 
#- ship trying to gain access to the deck of the ship. NateMagic hit them all off the side of the boat flinging them back into the water. They climbed through the cannons and dug through the hull of the ship to get on deck. NateMagic went up into the crows 
#- nest and poured lava down the side burning all those that tried to follow him up. They pillared up creating massive dirt walls while firing arrows at NateMagic. Undergeared and running out of arrows, NateMagic dove into the water and swam away from 
#- the town. 

Ttocs Khan:

Ttocs Khan was sprinting across town looking for NoxyD. NoxyD the mouth of the Jacks, saw him and he called on his men for backup, they were not close enough.
#- Ttocs Khan hammered NoxyD to the ground, squirming away slowly as the Khan approached him he shrieked, "HELP ME!". His cries were answered, the Khan raised his sword ready to end this silver tongued snake's life when a blue shining blade 
#- penetrated the Khan's chest. The Khan saw his soul pulled from his chest and he blacked out. 
#- Scout5555:

The youngest member of NateMagic's crew whom was picked up after he had helped NateMagic decorate the captin's quarters of the ship logged in to see the Jacks' whom he was brought up hating all of his life. He saw 
#- NateMagic dive off the edge of the ship into the blue water followed by showers of arrows. Scout looked around for allies, adrenaline pumping through his body when he heard a foul voice call on him. He could not tell who it was, it was someone strange. 
#- He saw the man and recognized him, NoxyD. He was shouting at him to surrender. Scout would never let this man take him without a fight. He pulled the bow back and let an arrow fly right at NoxyD. Pulling back again he felt a sharp pain in his side and 
#- blacked out. 
#- The Resolution:

The Jacks formed a treaty this time, with all Lazulian's present. NateMagic resented the treaty saying that allies would come to their aid and that the Jacks would not be able to defend against the onslaught.
#- Ttocs Khan had a change of heart, after the heat of battle he no longer wished to fight and kill. NateMagic respecting his leader backed down and contacted NoxyD telling him he would not pursue him. In this instant NoxyD took a shot at NateMagic 
#- asking him to join the Jacks and be the Jacks' Sheriff as they were working on a town. NateMagic declined. 
#- This is the original work of §oNateMagic§r. It has been transcribed on 01/05/13 by §oAce_of_Knaves§r for the benefit of Haven and the rest of Civcraft.

#- 